Kubernetes RBAC
================
To Access kubernetes api server we need to authenticate and authorize.
1.RBAC
2.ABAC
3.Node Authorization

Cluster information resides within ~/.kubeconfig/config
Certificate based authentication happens for user accessing a kubernetes cluster.
If the user provides a certificate signed by a valid certifcate authority than user is uthenticated.

1.Generate a private key
2.Construct CSR using the private key.
3.Request CA to provide certificate
using above info.

openssl x509 -req -CA ~/.minikube/ca.crt -CAkey ~/.minikube/ca.key -CAcreateserial -days 730 -in zyz.csr -out xyz.crt
kubectl config set-credentials xyz --client-certificate=xyz.crt --client-key=xyz.key






